.

  Summary: Strength Filtering Implementation

  What Changed

  Files Modified:
  - /core/models/query/_cypher_generator.py - Added min_strength parameter to both prerequisite chain methods

  Methods Enhanced:
  1. build_simple_prerequisite_chain() - Now filters by confidence AND strength
  2. build_prerequisite_chain() - Same enhancement for semantic relationships

  The Pattern:
  # Before (only confidence filtering)
  WHERE all(r IN rs WHERE coalesce(r.confidence, 1.0) >= $min_confidence)

  # After (confidence + strength filtering)
  WHERE all(r IN rs WHERE
      coalesce(r.confidence, 1.0) >= $min_confidence
      AND coalesce(r.strength, 1.0) >= $min_strength
  )

  Benefits Achieved

  | Benefit                   | Impact                                                |
  |---------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
  | Leverage existing fields  | Zero schema changes - strength already exists         |
  | Filter weak prerequisites | min_strength=0.7 eliminates tangential relationships  |
  | Better recommendations    | Show only critical prerequisites, not optional ones   |
  | Backward compatible       | min_strength=0.0 (default) includes all relationships |

  Usage Examples

  # Get CRITICAL prerequisites only (high quality + high importance)
  query, params = CypherGenerator.build_simple_prerequisite_chain(
      node_uid="ku.advanced_python",
      node_label="KnowledgeUnit",
      relationship_type="REQUIRES",
      min_confidence=0.7,  # Quality threshold
      min_strength=0.7     # Importance threshold - critical only
  )

  # Get all prerequisites (backward compatible)
  query, params = CypherGenerator.build_simple_prerequisite_chain(
      node_uid="ku.advanced_python",
      node_label="KnowledgeUnit",
      relationship_type="REQUIRES"
      # min_strength defaults to 0.0 (includes all)
  )

 ####  Next Steps (Phase 2)

  The big opportunity is weighted path ranking:

  -- Calculate path_strength as PRODUCT of all edge strengths
  WITH prereq, path,
       reduce(total = 1.0, r IN relationships(path) |
           total * coalesce(r.strength, 1.0)
       ) as path_strength

  RETURN prereq, path_strength
  ORDER BY path_strength DESC  -- Strongest paths first!

